-- South Africa Plans to Amend Mining Laws to Fix Weaknesses, Shabangu Says
-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s
-- 2011-02-07T08:00:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-07/south-africa-plans-to-amend-mining-laws-to-fix-weaknesses-shabangu-says.html
South African Mineral Resources
Minister Susan Shabangu said the country will amend its mining
laws to “correct” flaws.  The overlapping of prospecting rights involving  Lonmin Plc 
was caused by “weaknesses” in the country’s laws, she said in
a speech in Cape Town today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Carli Lourens in Johannesburg at 
 clourens@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
